headline: The 5 Most Interesting Analyst Questions From Ducommun’s Q3 Earnings Call
summary: Ducommun’s third quarter results met Wall Street’s revenue expectations but prompted a negative market reaction, with investors focused on the company’s sharply lower operating margin due to a substantial litigation settlement. Management attributed the quarter’s top-line growth to continued strength in the defense segment, particularly missiles and radar programs, which offset declines in commercial aerospace. CEO Stephen Oswald acknowledged ongoing commercial aerospace destocking as a key head
